<collectingCountry box="[469,604,420,445]" name="Madagascar" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[620,688,420,445]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1632,1654]" captionTargetBox="[177,1402,819,1580]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[150,1436,788,1611]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Geographic distribution records of Oecobius Lucas, 1846 in Madagascar (red) and Paroecobius Lamoral, 1981 (yellow) in the Afrotropical region. Red circle: Oecobius marathaus Tikader, 1962; red squares: Oecobius kowalskii sp. nov.; yellow square: Paroecobius private sp. nov.; yellow triangle: Paroecobius rico sp. nov.; yellow circles: Paroecobius skipper sp. nov.; yellow diamond: Paroecobius wilmotae Lamoral, 1981; yellow cross: Paroecobius nicolaii Wunderlich, 1995. Geographic coordinates for continental African Paroecobius were obtained from Wunderlich (1995) and from Google Earth, for P. nicolaii and P. wilmotae respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2611969/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="46" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,292,733]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,455,480]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Remarks.</emphasis>
The record of this species in 
<collectingCountry box="[658,793,455,480]" name="Madagascar" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
is not particularly surprising, since it has been recorded previously from the nearby 
<collectingCountry box="[459,579,492,517]" name="Seychelles" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Seychelles</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Saaristo, M. I." box="[593,750,492,517]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" pagination="99 - 126" refId="ref5528" refString="Saaristo, M. I. (1978) Spiders (Arachnida, Araneae) from the Seychelle islands, with notes on taxonomy. Annales Zoologici Fennici, 15, 99 - 126." type="journal article" year="1978">Saaristo 1978</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Santos, A. J. &amp; Gonzaga, M. O." box="[761,1034,492,516]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" pagination="239 - 252" refId="ref5563" refString="Santos, A. J. &amp; Gonzaga, M. O. (2003) On the spider genus Oecobius Lucas, 1846 in South America (Araneae, Oecobiidae). Journal of Natural History, 37, 239 - 252. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 713834668" type="journal article" year="2003">Santos &amp; Gonzaga 2003</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[1094,1189,492,517]" name="Réunion" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Reunion</collectingCountry>
islands (
<bibRefCitation author="Jacquot, M. &amp; Derepas, B. &amp; Deguine, J. - P." pageId="9" pageNumber="46" pagination="421 - 430" refId="ref5115" refString="Jacquot, M., Derepas, B. &amp; Deguine, J. - P. (2016) Seven newly recorded species and families of spiders from Reunion Island (Malagasy region) (Araneae, Araneomorphae). Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 121 (4), 421 - 430." type="journal article" year="2016">
Jacquot 
<emphasis box="[1380,1436,492,516]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
). This is the second widely distributed, synanthropic species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lucas" authorityYear="1846" box="[995,1101,528,552]" class="Arachnida" family="Oecobiidae" genus="Oecobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[995,1101,528,552]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Oecobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[1295,1433,527,552]" name="Madagascar" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. However, the previous record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lucas" authorityYear="1846" box="[525,670,564,588]" class="Arachnida" family="Oecobiidae" genus="Oecobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annulipes">
<emphasis box="[525,670,564,588]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">O. annulipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
requires confirmation, since this species has been confounded with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blackwall" authorityYear="1859" box="[151,250,600,624]" class="Arachnida" family="Oecobiidae" genus="Oecobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="navus">
<emphasis box="[151,250,600,624]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">O. navus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the literature (
<bibRefCitation author="World Spider Catalog" box="[440,751,599,624]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" refId="ref5909" refString="World Spider Catalog (2018) World Spider Catalog. Version 19.0. Natural History Museum Bern. Available from: http: // wsc. nmbe. ch (accessed 30 July 2018)" type="url" year="2018">World Spider Catalog 2018</bibRefCitation>
, compare 
<bibRefCitation author="Shear, W. A." box="[864,994,599,624]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" pagination="129 - 164" refId="ref5714" refString="Shear, W. A. (1970) The spider family Oecobiidae in North America, Mexico, and the West Indies. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, 140, 129 - 164." type="journal article" year="1970">Shear 1970</bibRefCitation>
: figs 29, 50, 51 with 
<bibRefCitation author="Santos, A. J. &amp; Gonzaga, M. O." pageId="9" pageNumber="46" pagination="239 - 252" refId="ref5563" refString="Santos, A. J. &amp; Gonzaga, M. O. (2003) On the spider genus Oecobius Lucas, 1846 in South America (Araneae, Oecobiidae). Journal of Natural History, 37, 239 - 252. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 713834668" type="journal article" year="2003">Santos &amp; Gonzaga 2003</bibRefCitation>
: figs 2–5).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
